	(text "Q1 - J310 JFET Stage\n\nJ310 is a depletion-mode N-channel JFET.\nTypical specs: Idss = 24-60 mA, Vp = -2V to -6V\n\nOperating Point:\nSource resistance = R2 (150Ω) + R14 (0-2kΩ trimmer)\nVgs = -Id × (R2 + R14)\nId = Idss × (1 - Vgs/Vp)² ≈ 5-7 mA (hot bias for lower noise)\n\nDrain Voltage Check:\nVd = 9V - Id × (R3 + R13)\nVd = 9V - (6mA × 570Ω) = 5.58V (Target: ~4.5V to 5.5V)\nNote: Tweak R14 if Vd is < 3V or > 8V.\n\nStage Gain: Av = 9-14 dB"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 52.832 159.512 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "7d290d58-02f4-46df-87b0-8ce1c2e1ee69")
	)
	(text "f_{c}=1/(2.pi.102R.470uF)\n  =~ 3.3 Hz"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 227.838 119.126 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "8d0a9065-265f-4ceb-8052-56f3802e45ef")
	)
	(text "A_{v} = 32-38 dB"
